text:
Hey everyone, I'm in the process of working through my Developer practicum and I had a quick question. How can I get the Global Footer partial to show up in the template's content panel on the page editor (see attached). I'm able to get the footer to show up there if I remove the header, but if I have both of them there it will only show the first one, the Header in this case. I've included my code for this page too. Would love a hand here I've been stuck with this longer than I was hoping lol.

```&lt;!--
    templateType: page
    label: Practicum Template
    isAvailableForNewContent: true
--&gt;
<!doctype html>
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;{{ content.html_title }}&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;meta name="description" content="{{ content.meta_description }}"&gt;
    {{ require_css(get_asset_url("/Practicum Theme - OG/CSS/layout.css")) }}
    {{ standard_header_includes }}
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;

    &lt;div class="body-wrapper {{ builtin_body_classes }}"&gt;

          &lt;!-- Start Header --&gt;
             {% block header %}
                  {% global_partial path="/Practicum Theme - OG/Template/Partials/header.html" %}
             {% endblock header %}
          &lt;!-- End Header --&gt;


       {% block body %}

          &lt;!-- Start of the DND Section--&gt;
              {% dnd_area "Main", class="main" label="Drag N Drop" %} 
                {% dnd_section background_color={
              r: 200,
              g: 200,
              b: 200,
              a: 1
            },
            padding={
              'top': 50,
              'bottom': 50
            }, vertical_alignment= 'MIDDLE' %}

              {% dnd_column  width=4,%}
                {% dnd_row %}
                  {% dnd_module "image" path="@HubSpot/image", flexbox_positioning="MIDDLE_CENTER", label="Featured Image" %} 
                  {% end_dnd_module %}
                {% end_dnd_row %}
          {% end_dnd_column %}

             {% dnd_column width=8, offset=4 %}
                {% dnd_row %}
                  {% dnd_module "rich_text" path="@HubSpot/rich_text", label="Featured Content" %} 
                     {% module_attribute "html" %}
                       &lt;h1&gt;Hello, world!
                       &lt;/h1&gt;
                       &lt;h3&gt;Thia is subheader text
                       &lt;/h3&gt;
                       &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipiscing elit, urna consequat felis vehicula class ultricies mollis dictumst, aenean non a in donec nulla. Phasellus ante pellentesque erat cum risus consequat imperdiet aliquam, integer placerat et turpis mi eros nec lobortis taciti, vehicula nisl litora tellus ligula porttitor metus. 
                       &lt;/p&gt;
                     {% end_module_attribute %}
                  {% end_dnd_module %}
                {% end_dnd_row %}
          {% end_dnd_column %}

          {% end_dnd_section  %}
              {% end_dnd_area %}
          &lt;!-- End of the DND Section--&gt;

          &lt;!-- Start People Listing Module --&gt;
          {% module "module_162817769815714" path='/Practicum Theme - OG/Modules/person_listing', label="person_listing" %}
          &lt;!-- End People Listing Module--&gt;

        {% endblock body %}

          &lt;!-- Start Footer --&gt;
             {% block footer %}
                  {% global_partial path='/Practicum Theme - OG/Template/Partials/footer.html' %}
             {% endblock footer %} 
          &lt;!-- End Footer --&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    {{ standard_footer_includes }}

  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;```

Hey <@U01JMV2N3AQ>! This is a great question. You've included your footer correctly in your template. Within the backend of the page editor, your footer won't show up in the Contents tab if there is no editable module in the partial. For example, my footer partial looked like this:
```&lt;!--
    templateType: global_partial
    label: Footer
    isAvailableForNewContent: false
--&gt;
&lt;!-- Begin partial --&gt;

&lt;footer&gt;
    {% global_partial path='./main-menu.html' %}
    &lt;p&gt;Â© Brooke Fisher 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/footer&gt;

&lt;!-- End partial --&gt;```
